SIMPLE: pecker
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pecker
<hw>Peck"er</hw> <pr>(p⟦ecr⟧k"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who, or that which, pecks; specif., a bird that pecks holes in
trees; a woodpecker.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An instrument for pecking; a pick.</def>
<rj><au>Garth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The penis; -- an obscene term for the male sexual
organ.</def> <mark>[Vulgar]</mark> ⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> penis, cock, prick, tool, peter, dick, shaft [all
but the first considered obscene].</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Flower pecker</b></col>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <cd>See under
<er>Flower</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>peckish</ent>⟦br⟧
